    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Actions required to arrive at a design. A design method is a structured approach or method for designing and building objects or structures. The techniques of a design process may include: defining problems, conducting research, brainstorming and conceptualizing, prototyping, selecting and finalizing, product analysis and improvement.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
